The paper focuses on a deep reinforcement learning approach for gathering hierarchical knowledge to accomplish a task, which is a common problem in many domains such as network penetration testing, targeted advertising, and medical diagnosis. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories. Additionally, the paper employs techniques such as Hierarchical Multiple-Instance Learning and hierarchical softmax to cope with the complex action space, which suggests that it may also belong to the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) categories. Finally, the paper demonstrates the method in a set of seven classification domains, which implies that it may also belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) category.
